bio.experienceSummary:
I'm a passionate childcare provider with a strong desire to positively impact children's lives. My 3 years of experience have given me the skills to provide a safe, stimulating, and nurturing environment for children of all ages. I'm patient, creative, and friendly, and I believe in open communication with parents.

I'm comfortable enforcing household rules and have experience with a variety of games and activities that promote learning and development. I'm confident I can provide your child with the care and attention they need to thrive.

I hold a college degree and am certified in CPR and First Aid. I also speak English and Spanish. I have a car and am comfortable with pets.

I look forward to meeting you and your child and providing them with the best possible care.

Hello! My name is Ashley, I'm a nanny/babysitter with about 8 years professional experience, seeking a full time position. I am a very sweet, caring, trustworthy and reliable person. I have a passion for children and I truly enjoy being with them. I have experience with kids ranging from 5 months old to 12 years old. In my current and past jobs I had a variety of duties ranging from changing diapers, feeding, nap time, potty training, to grocery shopping, running errands or pick up/drop offs. I have a lot of fun with the kids I take care of. I enjoy bringing them to the park, going for strolls around the neighborhood or doing a bunch of other outdoor and indoor activities. I am capable of light cooking, cleaning or homework help and I am willing to help out all around. You can rely on me to always be there and treat your child/children as if they were one of my own. I hope to hear from you soon!

description.displayText: We were fortunate to find Ashley as a nanny on care.com for our 1.5 year old daughter. Sadly we moved to another state and couldn't take her with us! Ashley is kind, loving, energetic, playful, honest and reliable. Since day one Ashley was nothing short of amazing. She kept up with our high energy toddler and was her "go-go" girl (as our daughter liked to say. Our daughter was thriving and her vocabulary was expanding daily by being around Ashley. She is punctual, had never missed a day of work and was easy to communicate with. Our home was left tidy and our daughter was safe and always had a smile on her face when she was around Ashley. She has years of experience and multiple references.

bio.experienceSummary: I've grown up taking care of kids as an eldest sibling and I am now a recent Tufts graduate with B. S in Clinical Psychology. I have experience with adapting age appropriate activities and enjoy finding those nearest to you. I worked full time at an educational childcare facility on the UES and have gained valuable knowledge on child based play for infants and toddlers. I now work full time as a foster care social worker and babysit whenever I have time to do so. I adore kids and animals, if you have pets that is not a problem! I can help with cooking preparation and light housekeeping. I enjoy helping others and can answer any questions about my experience or references.

description.originalText: My daughter loved her! She was so kind and playful with her

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Esther and I am currently a 22-year-old student at Kean University in Union, NJ. As an older sister, I have always known the responsibilities of taking care of my younger sibling and being in charge of a household from a young age. I have babysat for a family of 2 (7 years old and infant) for the last 7 years and I am proud to say that they have turned into happy and healthy young teenagers today! I also volunteered at a summer program during my high school years when I was a teacher assistant and worked with 1 1/2-4-year-old kids in a classroom setting. I am full of energy to help with a child's daily schedule and understand the importance of the development of these early years in their life. My passion for working with children is demonstrated through my work and my nurturing and caring personality.

description.originalText: She was punctual, polite, and great with our 1.5 year old son.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm Christlove, a dedicated and compassionate child care provider with a passion for nurturing the well-being and development of children. With various experiences either as a teacher's assistant or being a nanny to a beautiful family for 3 years and a background in community service, I bring a wealth of knowledge and skills to my work. 

I discovered my love for working with children at a young age and have since dedicated myself to providing quality care and support to children and families. With my warm and nurturing approach, I create a safe and stimulating environment where children can thrive. I am committed to fostering positive relationships with both children and parents, ensuring open communication and collaboration to meet the unique needs of each child.

As a passionate and experienced childcare provider with three years of experience, I'm dedicated to nurturing and supporting children's growth and development. My journey into childcare began with fulfilling babysitting roles, where I realized the positive impact I could have on children's lives. Since then, I've embraced the opportunity to support families by providing reliable childcare solutions.

My patient and calm personality, combined with my creative and imaginative nature, allows me to engage children in a variety of enjoyable and educational activities. I believe in fostering a nurturing environment where children feel safe and encouraged to explore their interests.

Communication is key, and I keep parents regularly updated on their child's day, either through verbal communication at pickup or via text or phone calls, whichever the parents prefer. As for household rules, I follow the parents' lead to ensure consistency and respect for their parenting style.

I currently work as a Speech Language Pathology. I am looking for a summer position for babysitting. I have been babysitting for a number of years and have references upon request. Please reach out to me if you are looking for a sitter for your children. I have experience with newborns all the way through teens. I am comfortable with as many children as you have and also have experience with children with disabilities as well. I have a car and valid drivers license as well. Please feel free to reach out with any questions you may have. I look forward to hearing back!

I have been working as a nanny for seven years. In addition to raising my own family, I am college educated and have trained as an EMT. I have had diverse life experiences and have tons of practical knowledge.

Ideally, I enjoy caring for bright children who enjoy reading and learning. I strive to introduce them to the world and guide them to new experiences. I am not a fan of TV as a means of childcare. I particularly enjoy interacting with people of different religions and ethnicities--learning works both ways!

My philosophy is that the parents and I need to work as a team. We all need to communicate about the children, the schedules, and our shared goals. If the parents and I share a common value system, the work flows and the children are the happy recipients.

description.displayText:
Ingrid is an extremely reliable, caring, neat and generous individual. She provided our family with Nanny services for 3 children aged 13, 11, and 9.
She is utterly trustworthy, very kind, and playful.
I would highly recommend her services to everyone.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Kerrie, I am 31 years old. I have been sitting for multiple families for nearly four years now on occasional, date night, and regular schedule. I have nearly 5+ years experience with nannying/sitting ages ranging from 3 months - 11 years old. The last family I worked with was a full time M-F 6am-4 p.m.  Caring for a 15-month-old and a 3-year-old. Duties included wake up, breakfast, nap time, changing, etc. Prior to that, I my work was also a full day 8am-5 p.m.  with a 15month old, I was responsible for all meals, bottle making, changing, nap time routine, etc. 
 I am also CPR and first aide certified, as well as my life guard certification. I am extremely reliable, caring, and have a flexible schedule with my own car and a clean driving record. I would love to talk more about possibly meeting and helping your family out. I can provide references if needed. Looking forward to hearing from you! 
Thank you!

description.displayText: Kerrie is a wonderful person and very patient. She is fun, friendly and athletic. I would definitely recommend her for child care.

bio.experienceSummary:
As the eldest of seven siblings and a mom to a 12-year-old, I've always had the privilege of nurturing children. My passion for fostering their growth led me to become a childcare provider. I also have a year of experience working at a daycare, which helped me develop strong skills in caring for children of various ages.

Patient, calm, creative, and friendly, I enjoy engaging kids in outdoor sports, board games, and educational activities. I'm also skilled at communicating with parents, keeping them informed about their child's day and addressing concerns.

Having been adopted, I understand the importance of a nurturing, supportive environment. I'm comfortable enforcing household rules, helping with light housekeeping, and supervising swimming activities. My goal is to create a positive, fun, and educational space for your child to thrive.

description.originalText: The best caregiver Ive had. Elizabeths dedication and professionalism have significantly impacted my day-to-day life.
